Parcel number, tax year and installment are both as string. All parameters are required. 
What needs to update:
amt_due = BalanceDue 
year_total = TotalAmountDue
Note: The block payment method is not in use currently. Do not code or store block status for now. 
To better understand the balance update logic (Implementation): 
After the first half due date, balances are rolled into the second half installment. Therefore, the first half wasn’t paid but the balance was all rolled into second half.
The total amount due that we’re providing will always be first half due plus second half due for the tax year.
Once first half is paid in a typical situation, our overnight charge build will set the amount due for the first installment line to zero and the year total will then reflect that reduction in balance.

Int Mod:
Goal
The goal of this int mod is to split the file mappings up for installment 1 and installment 2 and to better the user experience using TotalAmountDue. Splitting the file mappings will allow the biller to create installments with more precision (only have first half open until it’s due date). 
The existing file mapping labelled ‘Manatron - RE Annual with Two Coupons’ in CRM should stay in place, unaffected. This is in case the new solution cannot be implemented in time or is not to biller’s liking once tested.
Invoice File Changes
File Extension: .txt
File Delimiter:  '|'
Sample File (with new account balance field as last column)
File Transfer Frequency: As needed
There is no confluence documentation for the existing file mapping. Two new file mapping should be made (first installment, second installment). The existing file mapping should stay the same, in place. 
For the new file mappings, everything should match the existing file mapping except the following specified fields:
Position 0 is the first field in file
:
Split invoice creation into two file mappings
: one that creates first installments, the other creates second installments. Position 10 (value of 1 or 2) can be used to determine installment number. This field can be used to filter to the first or second installments in the file.
TotalAmountDue (IH Field 13)
: this will now always be pulled from the last field in the file (Position 16)
Custom 4 (IH Field 41): 
set to ‘Installment X Tax Year Y’ where X = 1 or 2 and Y is pulled from Position 8 in file.
InvoiceNumber
: Invoice number will be changed to 
TaxYear-InstallmentNumber-ParcelNumber
 (Position 8 - Position 10  - Position 0)
Invoice Update File
Biller can send adjustment file to two locations, file split not needed
Adjustment logic will stay the same. A new invoice update file is needed to update TotalAmountDue. If Position 11 for bill doesn’t match what’s currently set for TotalAmountDue, create a row in an invoice update file to update it. 
Note* the new field will be full account balance while first installment is due. Once first installment is past due, they will start sending it as just the full installment balance. IC to set Position 11 from file as TotalAmountDue throughout this process.
